### Example: 

```js
F.file('*.jpg', function(req, res) {
	// ... a transformation
	res.file('new-file-name.jpg');
});
```

```js
F.file('/img/', some_action1, ['.jpg', '.png', '#middlewareA', '#middlewareB']);
F.file('/process/invoice.txt', some_action2, ['#middlewareA', { custom: 'options for middleware' }]);

function some_action1(req, res) {
	// a custom content
	// !!! IMPORTANT !!! "this" is not a context of controller
}

function some_action2(req, res) {
	// a custom content
	// !!! IMPORTANT !!! "this" is not a context of controller
}```

This method creates file handler with the localization. It's very helpful for translation static `.html`, `.txt` and `.md` files. Modern web applications are combined with many template files and this method solves problem with the localization. The method is linked with `F.onLocale()` delegate. Supported flags:

- `compress` or `minify` enables compression (by default: `true`)
- `nocompress` disables compression
- `.extension` a file extension which will be accepted

```javascript
F.localize('/templates/*.html');

// Accept a new extension for the web server
F.accept('.hbs', 'text/html');
F.localize('/templates/*.hbs', ['nocompress']);

// With a sitemap identificator
// +v2.9.0
F.localize('#sitemapId/templates/*.html');
```

```html
http://0.0.0.0:8000/templates/settings.html   --> will be localized and minified
http://0.0.0.0:8000/templates/idontknow.html  --> will be localized and minified
http://0.0.0.0:8000/templates/ember.hbs       --> will be localized only```

Renders a view into the string. This method simulates the controller and renders HTML into the string.

`+v2.8.0` __Rendering view from URL address__:

```javascript
var response = F.view('https://www.totaljs.com/view.html');
if (response instanceof Function) {
	// Is called the only once because the second time the view is read from the framework cache
	response(function(err, response) {
		console.log('VIEW:', response);
	});
} else
	console.log('VIEW:', response);```

Creates a virtual route for merging static files. Method supports merging: JavaScript, CSS or HTML.

```javascript
// Merging files
F.merge('/merge.js', '/js/ui.js', '/js/default.js');

// Merging all files
F.merge('/merge.js', '/js/*.js');

// Merging files in themes:
F.merge('/merge.css', '=moderntheme/public/ui.css', '=moderntheme/public/default.css');

// Merging files in packages:
F.merge('/merge.css', '@packagename/public/ui.css', '@packagename/public/default.css');

// Merging files with an isomorphice code:
F.merge('/merge.js', '/js/default.js', '#isomorphicname1', '#isomorphicname2');

// External URL address:
F.merge('/merge.js', 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.2.1/jquery.min.js', '/js/default.js');

// Merging with blocks
F.merge('/manager.js', '/js/ui.js#manager', '/js/manager.js');

// With a sitemap identificator
// +v2.9.0
F.merge('#sitemapId/myfile.js', '/js/ui.js', '/js/manager.js');```

A custom mapping of static files. You can easily change a mapping static file. __IMPORTANT__: if you map some directory/file then the directory/file has to exist otherwise the mapping won't be work.

### Mapping files

```javascript
// http://0.0.0.0:8000/app.js --> server responds with app-homepage.js script
F.map('/app.js', '/hidden-in-public-directory/app-homepage.js');
F.map('/app.js', F.path.private('/app-homepage.js'));

// With a sitemap identificator
// +v2.9.0
F.map('#sitemapId/app.js', F.path.private('/app-homepage.js'));
```

### Mapping directories

```javascript
// all files
F.map('/custom/', '/hidden-in-public-directory/');
F.map('/custom/', '~/hidden-in-root-directory/');

// only images
F.map('/custom/', F.path.root('my-images'), ['.png', '.gif', '.jpg']);

// custom filter
F.map('/custom/', F.path.private(), function(filename) {
    return filename.match(/\.(jpg|gif|png|js)$/i);
});
```

### Mapping for packages

```javascript
// all files
F.map('/custom/', '@package_name');

// only images
F.map('/custom/', '@package_name', ['.png', '.gif', '.jpg']);

// custom filter
F.map('/custom/', '@package_name', function(filename) {
    return filename.match(/\.(jpg|gif|png|js)$/i);
});
```

### Mapping for isomorphic code

```javascript
// below file is linked to /isomorphic/my-isomorphic.js
F.map('/serverside.js', '#my-isomorphic');```

