## The definition

### PROPERTY: exports.id;

`optional` Can contain only the model name (it's the identificator name). A __default value__ for this property is the model filename without extension.

```javascript
exports.id = 'Model name';
```

### METHOD: exports.install;

`optional` `important` This is the initialization function of the module. This function is executed when the framework loads models.

```javascript
exports.install = function(options) {
	console.log('Hello from the model.');
};
```

### METHOD: exports.uninstall;

`optional` This function is executed when the framework uninstalls the model.

```javascript
exports.uninstall = function(options) {
	console.log('This model is uninstalled.');
};
```

### METHOD: exports.usage;

`optional` This function has to return exploitation of the module. [Example: Usage](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-usage).

```javascript
exports.usage = function() {
	return { requests: counter };
};
```

### A full example of model

The filename: `models/user.js`

```javascript
exports.id = 'user';
exports.version = '1.01';

exports.create = function(user) {
	// NoSQL embedded database
	NOSQL('users').insert(user);
};

exports.load = function(id, callback) {
	// NoSQL embedded database
	NOSQL('users').one().where('id', id).callback(callback);
}
```

Get the model in e.g. the controller action:

```javascript
function json_create_user() {
	var user = { id: Utils.GUID(5), alias: 'Peter Sirka' };

	// global alias:
	MODEL('user').create(user);

	// or
	F.model('user').create(user);

	this.json(user);
}```

`+v2.4.0`. __Components__ are a part of views and they can contain server-side implementation. `+v2.5.0` adds a support for groups and `v3.0.0` adds a support for async rendering.

```plain
Framework initialization:

01. Bundles
02. Modules
03. Packages
04. Models
05. Schemas
