```

---

__More informations__

- The component is a single `.html` file stored in `/components/` directory.
- Components are synchronous.
- They have same functionality like views.
- Components are compiled into the function.
- Supports localization `@(Translate me)`.
- Framework parses all inline styles from all components into the merged single file `/components.js` (compressed).
- Framework parses all inline scripts from all components into the merged single file `/components.js` (compressed).
- Links to static files are generated into the `@{head}` tag.
- [Download __Component example__](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/components)

---

## Single file declaration

The best practice is to store a server-side code and a client-side code of the component in the main component file.

- __IMPORTANT__ framework parses `<script total></script>` as server-side Total.js code

__Create `/components/newsletter.html`__:

```html
<script total>

	// +v2.5.0 optional
	exports.group = 'Name of group';

	exports.install = function() {
		F.route('/api/newsletter/', json_newsletter, ['post']);
	};

	// +v3.0.0
	// Optional ASYNC rendering helper
	exports.render = function($) {
		// $.repository
		// $.model
		// $.user
		// $.session
		// $.controller
		// $.query
		// $.body
		// $.files
		// $.options, $.settings --> will contain same value
		// $.callback(model); --> callback with model

		// !!! IMPORTANT !!!
		// "callback" returns a model which is used in the component "view"

		// For example:
		NOSQL('products').find().take(10).callback((err, response) => $.callback(response));
	};

	function json_newsletter() {
		var self = this;
		self.body.ip = self.ip;
		self.body.created = F.datetime;
		NOSQL('newsletter').insert(self.body);
		self.json(SUCCESS(true));
	}

</script>

<style>
	.newsletter { padding: 50px; background-color: #D0D0D0; border-radius: 4px; }
	.newsletter-input { font-size: 20px; padding: 20px; width: 100%; }
	.newsletter-success { padding: 50px; background-color: green; border-radius: 4px; color: white; }
</style>

<div class="newsletter">
	<div>Join to newsletter @{settings.key}:</div>
	<input type="text" class="newsletter-input" placeholder="Type your email address" />
</div>

<script>
	$(document).on('keypress', '.newsletter-input', function(e) {
		if (e.keyCode !== 13)
			return;
		var el = $(this).closest('.newsletter');
		$.post('/api/newsletter/', { email: this.value }, function(response) {
			el.replaceWith('<div class="newsletter-success">THANK YOU!</div>');
		});
	});
</script>
```

__Rendering__:

```html
<h2>Newsletter 1</h2>
@{component('newsletter', { key: 'Custom settings value', something: 100 })}

<h2>Newsletter 2</h2>
@{component('newsletter')}
```

## Separated declaration

__Create `/components/newsletter.html`__ (client-side):

```html
<style>
