## Synchronous programming not working

Probably you run node application without `--harmony` argument (__node +v0.11__). New Node.js version `+v6.0.0` doesn't need `--harmony` argument because supports generators by default.

```bash
$ node my-application.js
```

## Prevention for multiple requesting

If the server doesn't reply quickly, then the web browser can send the request again. We recorded the problem in __Chrome__ web browser.

### Total.js prevention

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
	// Prevention for multipe requests from one browser
	ROUTE('/', delay_operation, ['delay']);
};

function delay_operaiton() {
	var self = this;

	console.log('I am here.');

	setTimeout(function() {
		self.view('some-view');
	}, 10000);
}
```

### Important change for nginx

```lua
http {
	# VERY IMPORTANT FOR "DELAY" FLAG
	proxy_http_version 1.1;
}
```

## Too many open files

If the framework throws `Too many open files` exception then we have to enable [default-maximum-file-descriptors](#api~FrameworkConfiguration~default-maximum-file-descriptors) or increase the system limit via terminal `$ ulimit -v unlimited`.

```html
// The framework opens max. 10 files together and waits while they are not closed.
default-maximum-file-descriptors        : 10
```

