## Schema workflows

`+v2.3.0` `/workflows` file describes schema operations. In another words: you can map all `async` schema operations in the one file.

__Where do I have to store this file?__

```html
/controllers
/debug.js
/release.js
/workflows
```

## How does it work?

File: `/workflows` with:

```html
// Returns results as array from all operations
// name        : operation1 --> operation2 --> operationN

// Returns a result from `operation2`
// name        : operation1 --> operation2 (response) --> operationN
query          : query (response)
read           : read (response)
delete         : remove (response)
save           : workflow:'check'    -->        save (response)
signup         : workflow:'check'    -->        save (response)      -->      workflow:'confirmation'

// `(User)` means a fixed type of schema (so no other schema can call this workflow)
save (User)    : save (response)

// +v2.8.0 supports custom options
query          : query { approved: true } (response)
save           : workflow:'check'  { fields: ['phone', 'email'] }   -->     save { session: true } (response)
```

__List of all supported operations__:

- `query` - performs `SchemaBuilder.query()`
- `save` - performs `SchemaBuilder.save()`
- `read` or `get` - performs `SchemaBuilder.read()` or `SchemaBuilder.get()`
- `remove` - performs `SchemaBuilder.remove()`
- `workflow:'name'` - performs `SchemaBuilder.workflow(name)`
- `transform:'name'` - performs `SchemaBuilder.hook(name)`
- `operation:'name'` - performs `SchemaBuilder.operation(name)`
- `hook:'name'` - performs `SchemaBuilder.hook(name)`

## Controller

```javascript
exports.install = function() {

	// Responds with JSON `controller.$exec('save', controller.callback())`
	ROUTE('/api/user/save/',  ['*User --> save']);

	// Responds with `detail` view `controller.$exec('save', controller.callback('detail'))`
	ROUTE('/api/user/{id}/',  'detail', ['*User --> save']);

	// Calls action
	ROUTE('/api/user/query/', query, ['*User']);

};

function query() {
	// .$exec(workflow_name, [helper], callback(err, response)) --> performs `query` workflow
	this.$exec('query', this.callback());
}
```

## Important

- next operations are skipped if the `ErrorBuilder` contains only one error
- `/workflows` file can be installed from URL via `INSTALL('workflows', 'https://www....')`
- [Example: workflows](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/workflows)

## Blocks

The framework (`+v1.9.3`) has great mechanism for web development. Blocks can divide JavaScript, CSS or HTML into the multiple blocks. The blocks has to be used with `MAP()` or `MERGE()`.

- [Example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/blocks)

### Block definition

- each block has to begin via `@{block nameA, nameB, ...}` or `@{BLOCK nameA, nameB, ...}`
- each block has to ended via `@{end}` or `@{END}`
- the block has to be defined in comment clause
- the block name can contain multiple names
- the block tags has to be defined on separated lines (position of `@{}` is not important)

E.g. JavaScript:
```javascript
var common_values = {};

// ====================================
// @{BLOCK admin}
// ====================================
alert('ADMIN');
// ====================================
// @{END}
// ====================================

// ====================================
// @{BLOCK nameA, nameB}
// ====================================
alert('A');
// ====================================
// @{END}
// ====================================

// ====================================
// @{BLOCK nameB, nameC}
// ====================================
alert('B');
// ====================================
// @{END}
// ====================================
```

E.g. CSS:
```css
.common-styles {}

/*
 * @{BLOCK admin}
 */
div { background-color: red; }
/*
 * @{END}
 */

/*
 * @{BLOCK nameA, nameB}
 */
div { content: 'A'; }
/*
 * @{END}
 */

/*
 * @{BLOCK nameB, nameC}
 */
div { content: 'B'; }
/*
 * @{END}
 */
```

### How to enable blocks?

__Custom mapping:__

```javascript
// Enables "admin" block for admin.js
MAP('/js/admin.js', '/js/common.js#admin');

// Enables "nameA", "nameB" and "nameC" block for admin.js
MAP('/js/admin.js', '/js/common.js#nameA,nameB,nameC');
```


__Merging:__

```javascript
// Enables "admin" block for admin.js
MERGE('/js/admin.js', '/js/fileA.js', '/js/fileB.js', '/js/common.js#admin');

// Enables "nameA", "nameB" and "nameC" block for admin.js
MERGE('/js/admin.js', '/js/fileA.js', '/js/fileB.js', '/js/common.js#nameA,nameB,nameC');
```

